\details{
\subsection{Purpose}{

Signed \verb{/exchange} actions that move funds: between the spot and perp wallets
of one account (\code{usd_class_transfer}), to another address on Hyperliquid
(\code{usd_send}, \code{spot_send}, \code{send_asset}), out to the bridge
(\code{withdraw}), and between an account and its sub-accounts or a vault
(\code{sub_account_transfer}, \code{sub_account_spot_transfer}, \code{vault_transfer}). All
require a wallet signing key.

Inherits from \link{HyperliquidBase}. Every method supports both synchronous and
asynchronous execution depending on the \code{async} argument at construction.
}

\subsection{Signing}{

Most transfers are \strong{user-signed} actions over the
\code{HyperliquidSignTransaction} EIP-712 domain (each carries its own
\code{time}/\code{nonce} field, and \code{vaultAddress} is forced null on the wire). The
sub-account and vault transfers are \strong{L1} actions hashed and signed over the
Exchange domain. Amounts denominated in USD for sub-account/vault transfers
are scaled to micro-USD integers (x1e6) before signing.
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\url{https://hyperliquid.gitbook.io/hyperliquid-docs/for-developers/api/exchange-endpoint}
}

